# Write a helper function for computing deviation score
compute_dev_score <- function(recall_vec, correct_vec){
  length = length(recall_vec)
  dev_score = 0
  if (length == 1){
    return(dev_score)
  }
  for (i in 1:(length - 1)){
    j = i + 1
    dev_score = dev_score + abs((correct_vec[j] - correct_vec[i]) - (recall_vec[j] - recall_vec[i]))
  }
  return (dev_score)
}

# Compute Deviation Score
total_recall_wider <- total_recall_wider %>%
  rowwise() %>%  
  mutate(dev_score = compute_dev_score(recall_vec_NZ, correct_vec_NZ))

# Compute the length of each coarse-level list
total_recall_wider <- total_recall_wider %>% 
  rowwise() %>% 
  mutate(recall_vec_length = length(recall_vec_NZ))

# Compute the normalized Deviation Score (by dividing Deviation Score by the number of transitions in each list)
total_recall_wider <- total_recall_wider %>% 
  rowwise() %>% 
  mutate(norm_dev_score = dev_score / (recall_vec_length-1))

# Filter out excluded trial
total_recall_wider <- total_recall_wider %>% 
  filter(!(Subject == 2 & Narrative == "HC1_Aunt"))
total_recall_wider <- total_recall_wider %>% 
  rowwise() %>% 
  mutate(corr = abs(cor(recall_vec_NZ, correct_vec_NZ)))
total_recall_wider <- total_recall_wider %>% 
  mutate(order_correct = ifelse(norm_dev_score == 0, 1, 0))

Analysis 3: Recall Event Transition

3.1: Positive Transition Probability

Hypothesis: The probability of making positive transitions for within-event transitions in CS narratives (CS_within) will be lower than the percentage of positive transitions for within-event transitions in FS narratives (FS_within) or across-event transitions in CS narratives (CS_across).

# Construct a dataframe to store all the extracted recall pairs
complete_recallPairs <- data.frame(
  Subject = numeric(0),
  Narrative_Type = character(0),
  Narrative = character(0),
  Recall_lag = numeric(0),
  Script_lag = numeric(0),
  Correct = numeric(0),
  Recall_1 = numeric(0),
  Recall_2 = numeric(0),
  Script_1 = numeric(0),
  Script_2 = numeric(0),
  Script_coarse_1 = numeric(0),
  Script_coarse_2 = numeric(0)
)
complete_recallPairs
# Define function to extract recall pairs
extract_recallPairs <- function(recall_pair_df, list_name, narrative_type, narrative_name){
  for (i in 1:length(list_name)){
  # Access the recall dataframe of each Subject i
  current_recall <- list_name[[i]]
    # Traverse through the list
    for (j in 1:(nrow(current_recall)-1)){
      # Make sure index does not exceed list length
      row_1 <- current_recall[j, ]
      row_2 <- current_recall[j+1, ]
      
      Recall_val_1 <- row_1[1, "Recall_Order"]
      Recall_val_2 <- row_2[1, "Recall_Order"]
      Script_val_1 <- row_1[1, "Fine-level_index"]
      Script_val_2 <- row_2[1, "Fine-level_index"]
      Script_coarse_1 <- row_1[1, "Coarse-level_index"]
      Script_coarse_2 <- row_2[1, "Coarse-level_index"]
      
      new_row <- list(Subject = i, 
                      Narrative_Type = narrative_type,  # change type
                      Narrative = narrative_name,  # change name
                      Recall_lag = 0,
                      Script_lag = Script_val_2[[1, 1]] - Script_val_1[[1, 1]], #???
                      Correct = ifelse((Script_val_2[[1, 1]] - Script_val_1[[1, 1]]) > 0, 1, 0),
                      Recall_1 = Recall_val_1[[1, 1]], 
                      Recall_2 = Recall_val_2[[1, 1]], 
                      Script_1 = Script_val_1[[1, 1]],
                      Script_2 = Script_val_2[[1, 1]],
                      Script_coarse_1 = Script_coarse_1[[1, 1]],
                      Script_coarse_2 = Script_coarse_2[[1, 1]])
      
     recall_pair_df <- rbind(recall_pair_df, new_row)
     }
  }
  return(recall_pair_df)
}

sample_size = 32
# Define a function to turn each primitive studylist into real studylist in psifr
repeat_df <- function(study_df, sample_size){
  # repeat the study df for sample_size number of times
  stacked_df <- data.frame()
  for (i in 1:sample_size) {
    stacked_df <- rbind(stacked_df, study_df)
  }
  # create a column representing subject indexes
  subject_col <- rep(1:sample_size, each = 25) 
  # bind subject column to the dataframe
  final_df <- cbind(stacked_df, subject = subject_col)
  return(final_df)
}

HC1_Aunt_study <- repeat_df(HC1_Aunt_study_raw, sample_size)
HC2_Swimming_study <- repeat_df(HC2_Swimming_study_raw, sample_size)                                                                                                                                               
HC3_Morning_study <- repeat_df(HC3_Morning_study_raw, sample_size)
LC1_Shopping_study <- repeat_df(LC1_Shopping_study_raw, sample_size)
LC2_Cleaning_study <- repeat_df(LC2_Cleaning_study_raw, sample_size)
LC3_Zoo_study <- repeat_df(LC3_Zoo_study_raw, sample_size)
